comments:
Abolished 1.4.1926 and divided between the parishes of Eccup and 
    Leeds. See also Table 2, notes (d) and (e).

Created 1.4.1937 out of the parishes of Yeadon, Guiseley, Rawdon, 
    Menston, Hawksworth, Esholt and Otley. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished 
    area.

Abolished 1.4.1928 and added to the parish of Leeds. See 
    also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Bradford unparished area. See also Table 
    2, notes (d) and (i).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and added to the parish of Ilkley. See 
    also Table 2, note (d).

Renamed 1.11.1950 to become the parish of Norwood. See also Table 
    2, note (a).

Created 1.4.1926 out of the parish of Adel cum Eccup. Abolished 
    1.4.1928 and added to the parish of Leeds.
Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Idle, Aireborough and Baildon. See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Aireborough 
    and Ilkley. See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Aireborough, 
    Baildon and Ilkley. See also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, notes (b) and (g).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Ilkley, 
    Aireborough and Otley. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1.11.1950 by renaming the parish of Clifton with Norwood. 
    See also Table 2, note (j).

Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (f).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Aireborough, 
    Horsforth and Idle. See also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.4.1937 and divided between the parishes of Aireborough 
    and Idle. See also Table 2, note (a).

That part which until 1.4.1937 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Arthington and Horsforth. See also Table 2, note (g).
